First step: Compute the square of matrix \( M \), \( M^2 = M \times M \). For the matrix \( M = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 3 \\ 4 & 5 \end{pmatrix} \), calculate:

\[
M^2 = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 3 \\ 4 & 5 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 3 \\ 4 & 5 \end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix} (2 \times 2 + 3 \times 4) & (2 \times 3 + 3 \times 5) \\ (4 \times 2 + 5 \times 4) & (4 \times 3 + 5 \times 5) \end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix} 16 & 21 \\ 28 & 41 \end{pmatrix}
\]
